{
  "doc_id": "55714",
  "text": "Predictors of Response. Pretreatment serum ALT is the strongest predictor of response among HBeAg-positive patients. Pooled data from 4 studies with a total of 406 patients who received lamivudine for 1 year found that HBeAg seroconversion occurred in 2%, 9%, 21%, and 47% of patients with ALT levels within normal, 1-2 times normal, 2-5 times normal, and Ͼ5 times normal, respectively; the corresponding seroconversion rates for 196 patients in the placebo group were 0%, 5%, 11%, and 14%, respectively. [CITATION_1] Adverse Events. In general, lamivudine is very well tolerated. Various adverse events including a mild (2-to 3-fold) increase in ALT level have been reported in patients receiving lamivudine, but these events occurred in the same frequency among the controls. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Adefovir Dipivoxil (bis-POM PMEA, Hepsera)",
